    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I was thinking of a way to install an external profile into the correct place, both as a simple Python function, and as a shell command (`ipython profile copy /path/to/profile`).\n\nBut another approach might be for frameworks to provide a standard interface at an importable location so we could do: `ipython --pkgprofile zope` (which would try to find something like `zope.ipy_profile`). We probably don't want to depend on setuptools, though.\n"
  },
